-- Zimbabwe Considers $3 Billion Loan From China, Independent Newspaper Says
-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 2011-02-04T08:09:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/zimbabwe-considers-3-billion-loan-from-china-independent-newspaper-says.html
Zimbabwe is considering a $3 billion
loan offer from  China  that would be repaid with platinum
reserves and the proceeds of diamond sales, the Harare-based
Zimbabwe Independent newspaper said, citing unidentified people
in the government.  The government is divided on whether to accept the loan
because the platinum reserves are worth $40 billion, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  